1
00:00:04,438 --> 00:00:05,772
NAZE! Congratulations
on getting first place!

2
00:00:05,839 --> 00:00:07,174
This is all thanks to everyone!

3
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:09,109
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

4
00:00:10,110 --> 00:00:12,679
You've been on a roll
since Producer Azuma's departure.

5
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:15,449
We heard
he constantly abused his power

6
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:16,984
and looked down on the group members.

7
00:00:17,050 --> 00:00:18,685
Do you have any words for him now?

8
00:00:18,752 --> 00:00:20,821
Mr. Azuma is no longer
associated with NAZE.

9
00:00:20,888 --> 00:00:23,257
Please keep your questions
related to the song.

10
00:00:23,323 --> 00:00:25,225
We already told them he has
nothing to do with us now.

11
00:00:25,292 --> 00:00:26,827
Why do they keep asking
the same thing?!

12
00:00:32,132 --> 00:00:34,601
Where could Mr. Azuma be?

13
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:42,743
I've got it! Why don't you move?

14
00:00:42,809 --> 00:00:45,512
You guys can't stay in that
cramped and old house forever.

15
00:00:45,579 --> 00:00:46,880
I agree.

16
00:00:46,947 --> 00:00:48,148
Besides

17
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:49,616
NAZE is one of the top idols now.

18
00:00:51,418 --> 00:00:52,419
Ms. Nam.

19
00:00:52,653 --> 00:00:54,154
What should we do about the costumes?

20
00:00:54,221 --> 00:00:56,924
I doubt you'll be using the coats
and the kimonos again.

21
00:00:57,124 --> 00:00:58,458
Well, I guess you have a point.

22
00:00:58,525 --> 00:01:01,128
But the performance back then
was great, wasn't it?

23
00:01:01,194 --> 00:01:03,997
Yes, we got to wear
everyone's traditional clothes.

24
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:07,701
I was so moved when I saw
everyone's childhood photos.

25
00:01:08,669 --> 00:01:11,905
The origins of the ingredients
don't matter at all.

26
00:01:11,972 --> 00:01:15,642
We'll bring out our unique flavor
with our own power.

27
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:17,511
That's all that matters.

28
00:01:18,111 --> 00:01:20,414
Hey, those are the messages
we wrote back then!

29
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:22,416
DON'T BULLY TORINNER!

30
00:01:22,616 --> 00:01:24,384
Those kids were so cool, right?

31
00:01:24,451 --> 00:01:25,886
Please don't bully TORINNER!

32
00:01:25,953 --> 00:01:27,220
Instead of the anonymity
of social media

33
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:28,689
they'll write their true feelings

34
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:29,756
for TORINNER by hand.

35
00:01:29,823 --> 00:01:31,625
Mr. Azuma came up with this idea.

36
00:01:32,225 --> 00:01:33,493
Wait, what's this?

37
00:01:34,528 --> 00:01:35,996
It's Dad and Mr. Yamada.

38
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:38,966
I'm glad you made up with your dad.

39
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:41,768
You came to NAZE's
every live show, didn't you?

40
00:01:41,835 --> 00:01:45,205
Will you let my son join you again?

41
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,280
In the end...

42
00:01:55,382 --> 00:01:56,917
it was all thanks to Mr. Azuma.

43
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:59,586
He's the reason
we were able to make it this far.

44
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,202
Stop talking about him.

45
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:18,305
He abandoned us and just ran off.

46
00:02:19,539 --> 00:02:20,574
We know.

47
00:02:20,641 --> 00:02:24,077
Then forget about that horrible,
violent jerk!

48
00:02:24,678 --> 00:02:25,746
That's not it.

49
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:31,318
What I meant was, we know
why Mr. Azuma acted like that.

50
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:35,822
He didn't want to get in our way

51
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,959
so he tried to erase his presence.

52
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:45,632
It's too obvious.
He changed way too suddenly.

53
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:47,467
Kun, you knew that too, didn't you?

54
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:50,737
- But--
- It's enough, Kun.

55
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:58,912
Anyone would have been able to tell.

56
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,015
His attitude changed
way too suddenly.

57
00:03:02,616 --> 00:03:05,819
But Mr. Azuma told us

58
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:11,358
that it was his job to take
the best course of action for NAZE.

59
00:03:11,792 --> 00:03:14,461
If he had tried to deny the article
and caused a commotion

60
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:17,731
it wouldn't have been good for NAZE.

61
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:24,871
Mr. Azuma was the one who let us know

62
00:03:26,339 --> 00:03:29,443
it's okay for us to dream.

63
00:03:30,177 --> 00:03:34,681
Now, it's our turn
to help Mr. Azuma dream.

64
00:03:34,748 --> 00:03:36,917
I want to challenge myself
with even bigger dreams

65
00:03:37,484 --> 00:03:38,752
together with Mr. Azuma.

66
00:03:38,852 --> 00:03:39,853
Me, too.

67
00:03:43,490 --> 00:03:46,460
Kun. You feel the same, right?

68
00:03:55,202 --> 00:03:56,203
Yes.

69
00:04:02,342 --> 00:04:04,077
It must be nice to be young.

70
00:04:04,945 --> 00:04:07,948
But that guy is really stubborn!

71
00:04:08,014 --> 00:04:10,751
He'll refuse to come back for sure.

72
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:12,919
I agree with you.

73
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:17,624
Well...

74
00:04:18,692 --> 00:04:20,527
During our first live performance

75
00:04:21,528 --> 00:04:23,697
didn't he say that he would
do anything we say

76
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:26,933
if we filled up the National Stadium?

77
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:29,202
- Wait...
- He did.

78
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,705
- He said it. He did say it!
- Yes!

79
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:33,306
That's 80,000 people.

80
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:35,408
If you can fill up
the Japan National Stadium

81
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:37,177
I'll do anything you say.

82
00:04:37,244 --> 00:04:39,112
Let's make him keep his promise.

83
00:04:39,713 --> 00:04:41,948
- Wait, Minase, what do you mean--
- Guys!

84
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:46,119
- Let's hold a concert there!
- What?

85
00:04:46,253 --> 00:04:49,055
He said he'd do anything if you
filled up the National Stadium.

86
00:04:49,122 --> 00:04:51,925
It's the only way
to bring Mr. Azuma back.

87
00:04:51,992 --> 00:04:53,727
Wait a minute, Minase.

88
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:55,896
I hate to say this,
but that would be impossible!

89
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:58,265
That's 80,000 people.
Do you have a good plan?

90
00:04:58,532 --> 00:05:00,600
Azuma is gone now.

91
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:03,503
You're right. It's too difficult
for us to achieve that on our own.

92
00:05:07,774 --> 00:05:12,245
Are you saying that you can't
do anything without Mr. Azuma?

93
00:05:14,214 --> 00:05:18,451
Mr. Azuma said he'd give up
everything to protect NAZE.

94
00:05:19,186 --> 00:05:22,289
In that case, we cannot let him down.

95
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:27,160
Mr. Azuma had led us this far.
This time, let's work together

96
00:05:27,594 --> 00:05:30,363
and achieve something
that will surprise him!

97
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:39,873
What are you guys doing?

98
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,141
Let's have a meeting!

99
00:05:41,208 --> 00:05:43,009
What would Mr. Azuma do
to gather 80,000 people?

100
00:05:43,076 --> 00:05:45,512
Sorry, Ms. Nam.
We'll move another time.

101
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,781
Goodness!

102
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,822
You murderer!

103
00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:59,559
I am very sorry!

104
00:06:02,629 --> 00:06:03,864
It doesn't matter who it is.

105
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,999
Do it at all costs.

106
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:08,602
Find out what NAZE will do next

107
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:11,304
and Azuma's current whereabouts.

108
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:16,943
Hey.

109
00:06:18,311 --> 00:06:20,547
Are you guys not going to work
until I tell you to do so?

110
00:06:21,815 --> 00:06:22,949
Am I the only person here?

111
00:06:25,151 --> 00:06:29,089
Make yourselves useful to me!

112
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:30,624
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

113
00:06:36,029 --> 00:06:38,598
Hey, are you taking a break already?

114
00:06:38,932 --> 00:06:40,934
Losers have no time to rest.

115
00:06:41,201 --> 00:06:42,569
Move. Quick.

116
00:06:43,303 --> 00:06:44,671
Is he an amateur?

117
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:48,375
Nobody makes people
practice nonstop these days!

118
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,918
Hey! What's wrong?

119
00:06:58,318 --> 00:07:00,086
What are you doing? You'll die!

120
00:07:00,353 --> 00:07:01,354
Hey!

121
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,392
He's so dramatic.

122
00:07:06,493 --> 00:07:07,761
NAZE WILL HOLD A CONCERT
AT THE JAPAN NATIONAL STADIUM!

123
00:07:07,827 --> 00:07:09,729
We're NAZE!

124
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:12,265
We'll be holding a concert,
so please come!

125
00:07:12,332 --> 00:07:13,366
- Please come!
- Please come!

126
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,368
- What? NAZE?
- No way!

127
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:17,137
Please come to watch!

128
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:18,872
Don't push!

129
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:21,841
- Please don't push!
- Please don't push!

130
00:07:21,908 --> 00:07:23,076
Don't push!

131
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,311
Don't push!

132
00:07:24,377 --> 00:07:25,578
Please don't push!

133
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:27,647
- Nobody's pushing me, huh?
- Don't push!

134
00:07:27,747 --> 00:07:28,848
- We're NAZE!
- We're NAZE!

135
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:30,283
- We'll be holding a concert!
- We'll be holding a concert!

136
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:31,885
It will be
at the Japan National Stadium!

137
00:07:31,952 --> 00:07:33,653
- Please come and watch!
- Please come and watch!

138
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,588
We're making really slow progress.

139
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:37,724
Is there a more efficient way
to promote?

140
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:38,792
I've got it!

141
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:42,329
The video Mr. Azuma made for TGC

142
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:43,930
was played many times, right?

143
00:07:44,431 --> 00:07:46,599
He said he still
had a bunch of other video footage.

144
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:48,268
Maybe there's something we can use.

145
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:52,939
Please go slowly! Don't push!

146
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:54,674
Right, we worked backstage.

147
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:56,209
Look!

148
00:07:56,343 --> 00:07:57,978
We also handed out flyers.

149
00:07:58,044 --> 00:07:59,913
Right, that hurt.

150
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:02,115
Why was this filmed? Who filmed this?

151
00:08:02,182 --> 00:08:03,183
You were horrible.

152
00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:05,852
- Hey...
- Oh, this part!

153
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,688
It's insane,
no matter how many times I watch it!

154
00:08:08,755 --> 00:08:09,889
You guys should forget that exists.

155
00:08:09,956 --> 00:08:11,624
Still, I'm surprised you managed
to stay so calm.

156
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:13,960
Well, I'm an adult.

157
00:08:16,629 --> 00:08:18,598
Once more. Reina, do it again.

158
00:08:19,432 --> 00:08:21,101
One more time, Reina!

159
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,869
Is this Mr. Azuma's voice?

160
00:08:23,636 --> 00:08:25,171
Reina! One more time, Reina!

161
00:08:25,238 --> 00:08:26,239
It is.

162
00:08:26,306 --> 00:08:27,774
Oh, come on.
I wanted something dramatic.

163
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:28,842
What did you say?

164
00:08:28,908 --> 00:08:30,276
He's being so mean.

165
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:32,345
He was just enjoying it.

166
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,513
How annoying.

167
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:35,015
He had no idea how I was feeling.

168
00:08:36,950 --> 00:08:39,786
- She's impressive, though.
- You mean Minase?

169
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:44,090
I don't know if you can call it
her passion or obsession.

170
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:45,625
But she has exceeded my expectations.

171
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:47,827
She wrote up
that thick stack of information

172
00:08:48,028 --> 00:08:49,963
and visited so many companies.

173
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:53,633
I asked if she was ready to be
responsible for other people's lives

174
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:56,169
but I feel like
she taught me a lesson instead

175
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:58,505
and made me reflect on myself.

176
00:09:00,774 --> 00:09:01,908
Mr. Azuma...

177
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:07,013
Shall we watch the others?

178
00:09:07,313 --> 00:09:08,415
- Sure.
- Okay.

179
00:09:10,817 --> 00:09:12,385
Oh, it's the riverbed.

180
00:09:13,153 --> 00:09:14,788
I had no stamina back then.

181
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:16,656
It's so embarrassing.

182
00:09:16,923 --> 00:09:19,959
Yuya can be a little too serious,
but he's resilient.

183
00:09:20,026 --> 00:09:22,028
When he decides on something,
he will stick to it.

184
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:23,163
He will go far.

185
00:09:25,999 --> 00:09:27,801
Ato is the pillar of this team.

186
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:30,470
He's always thinking
about what the team needs.

187
00:09:30,804 --> 00:09:32,839
I want him to be
more self-assertive, though.

188
00:09:34,107 --> 00:09:37,377
Younki may appear mischievous,
but he's actually observant.

189
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:41,147
I can see he's trying to help Ato
see anything he may have missed.

190
00:09:41,981 --> 00:09:44,050
I'm honestly surprised
by Turn's ability.

191
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:47,153
He has the talent
to become a world-class dancer.

192
00:09:47,353 --> 00:09:48,888
I want to train him carefully.

193
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:51,124
As for Kaisei...

194
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:53,860
Kaisei is...

195
00:09:55,528 --> 00:09:56,529
Come on!

196
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,332
Harmony is the most important thing
in a team.

197
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:01,267
But it's not something
anyone can achieve.

198
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:05,238
Having him around eases the tension.
That's an extraordinary talent.

199
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:09,342
Do-hyeok is the youngest,
but he has a mysterious charm.

200
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:12,745
I'm excited to see
how much he'll grow in the future.

201
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:16,683
I like Kun's intense,
passionate hunger to succeed.

202
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:18,318
With that earnest attitude

203
00:10:18,384 --> 00:10:20,653
he'll be the one
to lead NAZE someday.

204
00:10:22,388 --> 00:10:25,425
Why don't you tell them
all that yourself?

205
00:10:25,592 --> 00:10:27,393
I'm not comfortable
with praising people.

206
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,528
What an edgelord.

207
00:10:30,396 --> 00:10:34,200
Continuing to do what you love
isn't always fun.

208
00:10:35,235 --> 00:10:37,537
But nothing you do is ever wasted.

209
00:10:38,571 --> 00:10:41,574
You may hit a wall, and you
don't get the results you want.

210
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,378
When you repeat something
that may seem pointless

211
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:47,914
you steadily build up experience
over time.

212
00:10:48,615 --> 00:10:52,685
The accumulated experience helps them
create their own unique weapon.

213
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,422
That's why
I won't praise them easily.

214
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:59,659
They have incredible potential.

215
00:11:00,193 --> 00:11:02,428
Until that potential
is fully unleashed

216
00:11:02,795 --> 00:11:05,999
I want to keep telling them
to aim higher and higher.

217
00:11:11,538 --> 00:11:12,539
Mr. Azuma...

218
00:11:15,275 --> 00:11:17,744
Turning the experience we've built up
into our weapons...

219
00:11:22,715 --> 00:11:23,883
That's it!

220
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:26,719
It's the special version
of Isn't She Lovely?

221
00:11:26,786 --> 00:11:28,588
Please learn it!

222
00:11:28,755 --> 00:11:30,156
One, two...

223
00:11:41,935 --> 00:11:43,102
What do you think?

224
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:44,337
- That seems easy enough.
- Right.

225
00:11:44,404 --> 00:11:45,638
I think we can do it if we try.

226
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:48,007
Let's do a dance challenge together!

227
00:11:48,074 --> 00:11:49,642
An 80,000-person dance relay!

228
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,144
Here we go!

229
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:57,717
SEARCH, 80,000-PERSON
DANCE RELAY

230
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:04,757
SEARCH, 80,000-PERSON DANCE RELAY

231
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,360
It's difficult!

232
00:12:07,794 --> 00:12:10,263
But this is our chance
to repay Mr. Azuma.

233
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:11,564
Don't you agree, everyone?

234
00:12:11,631 --> 00:12:12,632
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

235
00:12:12,699 --> 00:12:15,902
SEARCH, 80,000-PERSON DANCE RELAY

236
00:12:15,969 --> 00:12:17,370
- Act cute?
- Yes, like that.

237
00:12:18,004 --> 00:12:19,739
I'm going to film! Get closer!

238
00:12:19,839 --> 00:12:26,312
SEARCH, 80,000-PERSON DANCE RELAY

239
00:12:26,379 --> 00:12:32,118
SEARCH, 80,000-PERSON DANCE RELAY

240
00:12:32,218 --> 00:12:36,155
They're doing all this
to ask Mr. Azuma to return.

241
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:38,825
There's no way Mr. Azuma
would abuse his power.

242
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:43,062
Ms. Park, we'd like
to support NAZE as well.

243
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,031
But...

244
00:12:45,698 --> 00:12:49,102
I don't know what Mr. Choi
might do if you do that.

245
00:12:58,177 --> 00:13:00,346
It has increased so much!

246
00:13:00,413 --> 00:13:02,015
I'm so happy!

247
00:13:02,081 --> 00:13:03,283
Wow!

248
00:13:03,349 --> 00:13:06,185
- Look! Just look at the sales!
- Yes, I'm looking.

249
00:13:06,252 --> 00:13:08,087
APPEARANCE REQUEST,
COLLABORATION REQUEST

250
00:13:09,222 --> 00:13:12,358
The 80,000-person dance relay
was a great idea.

251
00:13:13,059 --> 00:13:15,995
It's because
Mr. Azuma complimented my dancing.

252
00:13:16,596 --> 00:13:18,498
Wait! Have a look at this!

253
00:13:18,564 --> 00:13:20,033
What? Is there a problem?

254
00:13:24,771 --> 00:13:27,273
I can't believe he made all these
in secret.

255
00:13:29,442 --> 00:13:31,110
He's so sweet.

256
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:38,951
I just received your title track song

257
00:13:39,018 --> 00:13:40,219
from a songwriter in the US.

258
00:13:40,286 --> 00:13:41,387
I really like it

259
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:42,689
so I want you guys to hear it now.

260
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:45,525
He summoned us here in the middle
of the night just for this?

261
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:47,260
This guy is insane.

262
00:13:47,327 --> 00:13:48,528
That is...

263
00:13:49,362 --> 00:13:50,496
not all I have for you.

264
00:13:51,364 --> 00:13:53,099
- Wait, he speaks Japanese?
- Well...

265
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,601
I used to work in Japan.

266
00:13:58,271 --> 00:14:00,106
It seems that NAZE
will be holding a concert

267
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,641
at the Japan National Stadium.

268
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:04,410
Yes, we've verified that information.

269
00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:06,512
On the same day

270
00:14:07,714 --> 00:14:11,150
TORINNER will hold a concert
at Tokyo Dome.

271
00:14:11,384 --> 00:14:12,985
- What?
- Tokyo...

272
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:15,221
Congratulations on your dome debut.

273
00:14:15,288 --> 00:14:17,023
Please wait a minute, Mr. Choi!

274
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,424
We have only a few songs.

275
00:14:18,491 --> 00:14:21,060
That will not be enough
to satisfy our fans!

276
00:14:21,127 --> 00:14:22,695
Besides, we don't have enough time--

277
00:14:22,762 --> 00:14:23,896
Don't talk back to me!

278
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:26,833
I'm not asking for your opinions.

279
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:29,235
You're just going to do as I say!
You hear me?

280
00:14:30,336 --> 00:14:32,271
Just look forward to it.

281
00:14:33,072 --> 00:14:36,909
I'm going to crush NAZE for you.

282
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:51,090
Goodness, the snow is heavy.

283
00:14:51,157 --> 00:14:53,326
It's going to make the roof collapse.

284
00:14:53,993 --> 00:14:55,595
Please let me clear the snow.

285
00:14:58,331 --> 00:15:00,800
There's no reason for you to do that.
Now leave!

286
00:15:00,867 --> 00:15:01,934
I am sorry.

287
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:04,470
I've been thinking about
what I can do

288
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:05,738
but nothing comes to mind.

289
00:15:05,805 --> 00:15:07,073
Please, at least let me help--

290
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:08,574
I don't care about what you think!

291
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:18,918
GRADUATION CEREMONY

292
00:15:29,128 --> 00:15:30,897
WE'LL WIN THE BEST NEW ARTIST AWARD
AT MAMA!

293
00:15:30,963 --> 00:15:32,131
Riku...

294
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:37,303
Hey! It's dangerous! Get down!

295
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:40,006
Just stop it and come down.

296
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:42,909
Don't worry, I'll be careful.

297
00:15:43,743 --> 00:15:46,045
Hey, sir, who is that guy?

298
00:15:47,713 --> 00:15:48,714
No idea.

299
00:15:53,986 --> 00:15:55,855
It's looking good!

300
00:15:56,055 --> 00:15:59,358
At this rate, we might be able
to fill up the stadium!

301
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:03,129
What?

302
00:16:03,563 --> 00:16:04,664
At Tokyo Dome?

303
00:16:08,201 --> 00:16:09,836
It's on the same day as our concert.

304
00:16:09,902 --> 00:16:11,137
TORINNER'S CONCERT AT TOKYO DOME!

305
00:16:11,204 --> 00:16:14,006
Darn it! They're here
to get in our way again!

306
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:20,480
Where is Mr. Azuma?

307
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:21,547
We mustn't.

308
00:16:21,914 --> 00:16:23,616
We can't rely on Mr. Azuma forever.

309
00:16:24,050 --> 00:16:25,117
I know.

310
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:27,720
I know, but...

311
00:16:29,922 --> 00:16:31,524
I like NAZE

312
00:16:32,024 --> 00:16:36,829
but there is no way I can betray Ryo!

313
00:16:36,896 --> 00:16:38,798
I was going to go
to the National Stadium!

314
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:40,600
Why does TORINNER's
first Tokyo Dome concert

315
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,335
have to happen on the same day?

316
00:16:44,237 --> 00:16:46,606
Flowers never betray me.

317
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:49,408
The more I care for them

318
00:16:50,142 --> 00:16:51,878
the better they grow.

319
00:16:55,081 --> 00:16:56,916
I hope TORINNER will be the same.

320
00:16:58,117 --> 00:17:00,019
Hey, turn on the studio cameras.

321
00:17:03,055 --> 00:17:04,056
What's going on?

322
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:06,592
Where did they go?
The concert is just days away!

323
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:08,127
They might be taking a break.

324
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:09,862
Who allowed them to?

325
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:11,364
Make them resume their practice.

326
00:17:11,831 --> 00:17:12,899
Yes, sir.

327
00:17:24,443 --> 00:17:25,545
Where are you going?

328
00:17:29,448 --> 00:17:32,351
I've decided to live the way I want.

329
00:17:37,156 --> 00:17:38,157
This is bad.

330
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:39,592
So many people have canceled
their tickets.

331
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:42,228
At this rate,
forget about bringing Azuma back.

332
00:17:42,295 --> 00:17:44,430
We'll go bankrupt from huge losses.

333
00:17:44,697 --> 00:17:45,698
Yes?

334
00:17:53,172 --> 00:17:54,340
What do you want?

335
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:03,349
You're still at it?

336
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:05,184
Sorry, I couldn't do it properly.

337
00:18:05,251 --> 00:18:08,588
Sir, let him rest inside.
Otherwise, he'll die!

338
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:10,523
This guy is none of my concern.

339
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:14,594
Don't be ridiculous!
That would make you a murderer!

340
00:18:15,895 --> 00:18:17,296
I'll fetch you a patch.

341
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:32,878
GRADUATION CEREMONY

342
00:18:39,085 --> 00:18:43,522
My arrogance drove Riku to his death.

343
00:18:45,057 --> 00:18:46,392
I am really sorry.

344
00:18:48,294 --> 00:18:50,096
I had no idea that he had passed away

345
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,365
so I was late in coming to see you.

346
00:18:57,937 --> 00:18:59,238
Here's a patch for you.

347
00:19:00,506 --> 00:19:02,208
Shall I put it on your back for you?

348
00:19:02,274 --> 00:19:04,076
No, it's okay. Thank you.

349
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:05,778
Don't overdo it, all right?

350
00:19:05,945 --> 00:19:09,382
There are things you can
and cannot do in a snowy region.

351
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:10,816
Right, Izaburo?

352
00:19:16,455 --> 00:19:20,226
Hey, do you know about
the Snow Festival's sky lanterns?

353
00:19:21,127 --> 00:19:22,328
No, I don't.

354
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:27,099
We get so much snow around here,
so there's no risk of forest fires.

355
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:31,137
That's why we can
send up lanterns like this.

356
00:19:32,405 --> 00:19:36,542
It started as a prayer for recovery
from the earthquake in this town.

357
00:19:37,143 --> 00:19:40,146
But to this day, people continue
to write their wishes on them.

358
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:44,483
Riku loved this festival
since he was a kid--

359
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,152
Keep your mouth shut!

360
00:19:46,218 --> 00:19:47,520
Come on! What's the harm?

361
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:50,589
Even after Riku became a celebrity

362
00:19:50,656 --> 00:19:52,625
he would still come back
for the Snow Festival.

363
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:55,027
And then he'd brag to me.

364
00:19:55,728 --> 00:19:59,231
He said his dream came true because
of his grandpa, who raised him...

365
00:20:00,566 --> 00:20:02,334
and a producer named Mr. Azuma.

366
00:20:02,802 --> 00:20:04,437
He said
it was thanks to both of them.

367
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:13,946
You are Azuma, aren't you?

368
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:18,617
Yes.

369
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:23,856
Take a look at this picture.

370
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:26,559
WE'LL WIN THE BEST NEW ARTIST AWARD
AT MAMA!

371
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:30,029
He was really grateful to you.

372
00:20:30,096 --> 00:20:31,130
Stop it!

373
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:35,067
This jerk killed Riku.

374
00:20:35,134 --> 00:20:38,904
He doesn't look like someone
who would push a person to his death.

375
00:20:39,138 --> 00:20:42,908
I'm sure you also remember
how Riku was back then.

376
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:49,014
He looked really bright.

377
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:51,884
WE'LL WIN THE BEST NEW ARTIST AWARD
AT MAMA!

378
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,592
Where did they go?

379
00:20:59,792 --> 00:21:01,694
Where is TORINNER? Answer me!

380
00:21:03,195 --> 00:21:05,598
- I don't know.
- You idiots!

381
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:07,199
Where's that guy?

382
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,635
I ordered him to look for them!

383
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,670
Where did he go?!

384
00:21:15,007 --> 00:21:16,275
By "that guy"...

385
00:21:17,977 --> 00:21:19,411
who are you referring to?

386
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:22,214
What?

387
00:21:23,182 --> 00:21:25,651
Is there even a need for me
to memorize your names?

388
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:28,187
We aren't...

389
00:21:29,822 --> 00:21:31,023
your puppets.

390
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:32,158
Are you crazy?

391
00:21:32,424 --> 00:21:37,296
You only move when I tell you to.

392
00:21:37,363 --> 00:21:39,331
You're nothing more than puppets!

393
00:21:41,567 --> 00:21:42,568
What was that?

394
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:44,403
TORINNER IS NOW LIVE

395
00:21:45,738 --> 00:21:46,939
Hello, everyone.

396
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:49,008
- We're TORINNER.
- We're TORINNER.

397
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:50,109
What's this?

398
00:21:50,176 --> 00:21:52,077
This morning, we announced that

399
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,846
we would be holding a concert
at Tokyo Dome.

400
00:21:53,913 --> 00:21:56,115
I feel so blessed
seeing my favorites together

401
00:21:56,182 --> 00:21:57,383
However, we'll be canceling it.

402
00:21:57,449 --> 00:21:58,584
I love you guys

403
00:21:59,218 --> 00:22:01,453
What are these morons talking about?

404
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,989
Instead, we plan
to make a guest appearance

405
00:22:04,456 --> 00:22:06,725
at NAZE's concert
at the Japan National Stadium.

406
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:10,663
Wait, aren't you guys rivals?

407
00:22:17,269 --> 00:22:19,638
NAZE are our friends

408
00:22:19,705 --> 00:22:21,273
so please come to the concert.

409
00:22:21,574 --> 00:22:24,677
- We look forward to seeing you!
- We look forward to seeing you!

410
00:22:24,844 --> 00:22:26,178
What the heck was that?!

411
00:22:32,952 --> 00:22:35,054
Are you guys going to be okay?

412
00:22:35,521 --> 00:22:37,122
Who knows? But...

413
00:22:39,225 --> 00:22:43,329
We need to take charge
of our own lives.

414
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:06,018
You are one of SS's members...

415
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:10,322
Ji-hoon! Why are you here?

416
00:23:15,461 --> 00:23:16,595
Mr. Izaburo.

417
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:18,631
Mr. Azuma.

418
00:23:19,899 --> 00:23:21,066
I am so sorry!

419
00:23:21,901 --> 00:23:24,336
I lied.

420
00:23:24,837 --> 00:23:27,339
I was the one
who drove Riku to his death.

421
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:30,609
Mr. Azuma had nothing to do with it.

422
00:23:32,378 --> 00:23:33,812
Get TORINNER here now.

423
00:23:33,979 --> 00:23:34,980
Now!

424
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:39,551
What's this?

425
00:23:39,785 --> 00:23:41,153
What are you scumbags doing?

426
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,554
Hey!

427
00:23:43,656 --> 00:23:44,924
Do you...

428
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:48,060
know my name?

429
00:23:48,127 --> 00:23:49,495
I don't care what your name is!

430
00:23:49,561 --> 00:23:50,829
I am...

431
00:23:51,597 --> 00:23:52,865
Seung-ho.

432
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:54,066
I am Ju-heon.

433
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:55,668
I'm Min-gyu.

434
00:23:55,734 --> 00:23:57,202
My name is Kyung-ju.

435
00:23:57,269 --> 00:24:00,572
We've decided that we want to live
like normal humans.

436
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:02,141
Please excuse us.

437
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:04,543
Hey.

438
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:05,611
Hey!

439
00:24:05,678 --> 00:24:06,679
Hey!

440
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:09,715
It was Mr. Choi Ki-young

441
00:24:09,782 --> 00:24:12,851
who kicked Mr. Azuma
out of SEVEN SEAS.

442
00:24:12,918 --> 00:24:14,720
Choi did that? Why?

443
00:24:15,254 --> 00:24:19,191
Ever since you became SS's producer

444
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:23,195
Choi thought about
getting revenge on you.

445
00:24:23,262 --> 00:24:24,430
Revenge?

446
00:24:24,997 --> 00:24:28,167
A big round of applause
for Producer Azuma!

447
00:24:28,734 --> 00:24:32,371
Mr. Azuma already had a track record
of producing another popular group

448
00:24:32,705 --> 00:24:34,673
and he was always the one
who stood out.

449
00:24:35,174 --> 00:24:37,710
On the other hand, Choi often did
the unglamorous tasks

450
00:24:37,776 --> 00:24:39,445
like schedule coordination
and apologizing to business partners.

451
00:24:39,511 --> 00:24:42,147
I'm impressed!
How did you get that filmed there?

452
00:24:42,214 --> 00:24:43,615
Come on, anyone can rent that place.

453
00:24:43,682 --> 00:24:45,017
They allowed it
because of you, Azuma.

454
00:24:45,084 --> 00:24:46,852
As SS became more successful

455
00:24:46,919 --> 00:24:48,487
Choi started asserting

456
00:24:48,554 --> 00:24:50,122
his own opinions.

457
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:51,890
The company will never allow this!

458
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:53,959
We've been doing it like this.

459
00:24:54,026 --> 00:24:56,662
But they would always listen
to Mr. Azuma's ideas.

460
00:24:56,729 --> 00:24:58,030
Thank you.

461
00:24:58,097 --> 00:25:01,300
That was when Choi overheard
their boss's conversation.

462
00:25:01,667 --> 00:25:05,337
A boring guy like Choi should stay
quietly in Azuma's shadow.

463
00:25:05,404 --> 00:25:07,539
He made the meeting longer
and wasted our time.

464
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:13,278
So, Choi fabricated a story about

465
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:14,813
Mr. Azuma abusing his power.

466
00:25:15,948 --> 00:25:18,617
He filmed us with a hidden camera
during practice

467
00:25:18,684 --> 00:25:21,587
and edited it so that it looked like
Mr. Azuma assaulted our members.

468
00:25:21,754 --> 00:25:23,322
Then, he leaked it to the press.

469
00:25:23,422 --> 00:25:24,590
What were you thinking?

470
00:25:24,656 --> 00:25:26,458
Are you trying to ruin SS?

471
00:25:27,059 --> 00:25:28,994
Before the incident

472
00:25:29,061 --> 00:25:30,496
spiraled out of control

473
00:25:30,596 --> 00:25:32,031
Mr. Azuma had a talk with us.

474
00:25:32,097 --> 00:25:33,866
I'm quitting my job as a producer.

475
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:36,301
I'm tired of looking after you.

476
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,070
I'm done with you. Do it yourselves.

477
00:25:38,137 --> 00:25:39,304
What are you talking about?

478
00:25:39,371 --> 00:25:41,173
Are you going to abandon us now?

479
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,474
You don't care about SS?

480
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:44,109
- Are you running away now?
- You traitor!

481
00:25:44,176 --> 00:25:46,612
Are you trying to ruin our lives?

482
00:25:46,678 --> 00:25:48,347
Everything went
according to Choi's plan

483
00:25:48,881 --> 00:25:51,650
and Mr. Azuma was blacklisted
from the industry.

484
00:25:52,151 --> 00:25:55,921
No way. He went that far
out of mere jealousy?

485
00:25:56,422 --> 00:25:59,391
Choi became our chief producer,
and he brought to us...

486
00:25:59,625 --> 00:26:00,959
Are you kidding me?

487
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,629
...a concept completely different

488
00:26:03,695 --> 00:26:04,763
from Mr. Azuma's vision.

489
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:07,966
So our leader, Riku,
and the rest of us strongly objected.

490
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,903
You want us to perform
such a lame song? Are you serious?

491
00:26:10,969 --> 00:26:12,638
Mr. Azuma wouldn't have
given us something like this.

492
00:26:12,704 --> 00:26:14,006
That's right. It's not going to sell.

493
00:26:14,073 --> 00:26:16,175
Shut up! I am the producer.

494
00:26:16,241 --> 00:26:18,243
Shut up and follow my orders!

495
00:26:19,611 --> 00:26:21,847
We stopped talking
to each other after that.

496
00:26:22,114 --> 00:26:26,752
It was impossible for us
to accept Choi's producing methods.

497
00:26:27,519 --> 00:26:29,421
And then...

498
00:26:30,489 --> 00:26:32,524
For some reason

499
00:26:34,193 --> 00:26:36,395
the other members found out
about my secret.

500
00:26:38,097 --> 00:26:40,933
We had been living together
for ten years

501
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:44,736
but there was a secret
that I couldn't tell them.

502
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,372
It got out somehow.

503
00:26:49,074 --> 00:26:50,075
My secret is that...

504
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:54,913
I am gay.

505
00:26:55,814 --> 00:26:57,416
Darn you! Why did you tell them?

506
00:26:57,483 --> 00:26:59,685
So I confronted Riku.

507
00:27:00,152 --> 00:27:02,888
After all,
he was the only one I had told.

508
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:04,490
It really wasn't me!

509
00:27:04,556 --> 00:27:07,292
I blamed him again and again.

510
00:27:07,359 --> 00:27:09,862
You're the most horrible person.
You don't deserve to live!

511
00:27:09,928 --> 00:27:12,097
You ruined everything.
Get out of my sight!

512
00:27:14,199 --> 00:27:17,402
SS disbanded right after that.

513
00:27:18,137 --> 00:27:19,805
A few months later...

514
00:27:20,172 --> 00:27:21,173
Ji-hoon!

515
00:27:23,909 --> 00:27:24,943
Riku...

516
00:27:25,310 --> 00:27:26,645
Riku died.

517
00:27:29,448 --> 00:27:32,885
I suppose Riku's death
was unexpected, even for Choi.

518
00:27:33,719 --> 00:27:35,988
He promised that he'd hire me
as his secretary

519
00:27:36,054 --> 00:27:38,490
and with good pay.

520
00:27:40,526 --> 00:27:42,094
